cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the construction of a network that is difficult to defeat with adversarial examples, which is a common problem in computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are the most likely categories. The paper also discusses the insights into how deep networks work, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with the security aspect of ML, which could place it in cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper proposes a novel application of the SafetyNet architecture, which could also place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
